<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-193] Wide Striping feature flag is incorrect in documentation</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-193</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Section 5.3.3, page 27 (of the PDF Manual) states that you need to use the tune2fs -O option for large_xattr &amp;#8211; when in fact it is ea_inode. Tune2fs -o large_xattr fails because it&apos;s an unknown option. I asked James Simmons and the mkfs.lustre option for large_xattr fails as well. We recently had to enable this on our Lustre 2.4 filesystem because we forgot to enable it at format time. &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="21699">LUDOC-193</key>
            <summary>Wide Striping feature flag is incorrect in documentation</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://jira.whamcloud.com/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&amp;avatarId=11303&amp;avatarType=issuetype">Bug</type>
